headline: Retail sales, Dell earnings, pending home sales: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Tuesday, November 25, including the release of September's retail sales, Producer Price Index (PPI) survey, and consumer confidence data; quarterly earnings from companies like Alibaba (BABA, 9988.HK), Kohl's (KSS), and Dell Technologies (DELL); and the latest print of US pending home sales. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Is Best Buy's (BBY) Advertising Push Shifting Its Profit Model for the Long Term?
summary: Best Buy released its third-quarter earnings, providing insights into its operational performance and growth strategies amid a busy reporting week for the retail sector. Attention was drawn to the company's efforts to balance low-margin hardware sales with a growing, higher-margin advertising business that could significantly influence profit drivers. We'll explore how investor focus on Best Buy's advertising network could reshape the company's long-term investment case and margin...
